1
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,240
The Shu road is steep,

2
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,480
harder than climbing green mountains.

3
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,600
Cut it out.

4
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,840
You're reading it wrong.

5
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,000
You scared me to death.

6
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,760
I thought my mom suddenly came back.

7
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,400
Officer Ran, what is it?

8
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,360
<i>GAOKAO SECRETS</i>
HIGH SCHOOL CHINESE FULL REVIEW GUIDE

9
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:19,840
Du Mingliang.

10
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,120
Someone saw you hanging
around the building all day,

11
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,160
acting suspicious.

12
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,280
They think you've been
stealing women's underwear,

13
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,560
stockings, and high heels.

14
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:28,840
Who's spreading that nonsense?

15
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:32,120
Officer Ran, I'm not some fetishist.

16
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,560
My mom's going through menopause.

17
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,080
She keeps nagging me about gaming,

18
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,680
so now I spend my days

19
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:37,920
playing cat and mouse
with her in the hallway.

20
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,640
Do you remember?

21
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,040
Back then, you even mistook me
for a Pattia hostess.

22
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,920
I swear on everything I own,

23
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,360
I'm absolutely not a pervert.

24
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,360
Then who do you think it is?

25
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,520
Du Mingliang.

26
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,480
Du Mingliang. You've got some nerve.

27
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:15,400
You played games until you ranked
dead last in school,

28
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:18,519
and now you've even brought
the police right to the door.

29
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,000
You really think
I won't beat you senseless?

30
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:20,760
- Please…
- Beat you senseless?

31
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:23,000
- Mrs. Du, it's a misunderstanding.
- Officer Ran,

32
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:26,120
did he do something wrong?

33
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,920
It's a misunderstanding.
I'm just here to ask Du a few questions.

34
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,280
About what?

35
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,800
It's about…

36
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,640
The severed head case?

37
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,840
Let me tell you,

38
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,160
years ago,

39
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,560
I did see Xu Zhihong.

40
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:52,800
When?

41
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,800
It should've been

42
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:57,320
before the Hong Kong handover.

43
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:01,280
Back then, Xu Zhihong ran to 1713,

44
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,080
Qihuang Clinic,
to argue with Zhang Ersong.

45
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:07,000
I just happened to pass by and heard

46
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:10,240
him shouting inside
about exposing something.

47
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,280
This Zhang Ersong

48
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,960
is Master Zhang from Qihuang Clinic.

49
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,680
What Master Zhang?

50
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,840
He's nothing but a con artist
who's done time.

51
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:23,200
I'm from Langzhong, same as him.

52
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:26,000
So Qihuang Clinic was shut down

53
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:27,840
because Xu Zhihong exposed him?

54
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,760
Shut down? Not at all.

55
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,280
They just moved
to a bigger place to expand.

56
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,360
Now it's a large clinic.

57
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,920
What's it called?

58
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,400
Songbentang.

59
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,960
I've lived here for over 20 years.

60
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:46,600
Back when Xu's mother was still alive,
we had some contact.

61
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,720
Ever since Xu died in a mountain accident,

62
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,880
he started borrowing money everywhere.

63
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,520
I didn't dare keep in touch
with them anymore.

64
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,400
Can you think back again,

65
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,640
before the 1997 handover of Hong Kong,

66
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:00,680
did anything unusual
happen in the Xu family?

67
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,000
Unusual?

68
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:05,880
Unusual…

69
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,520
Yes, there was something unusual.

70
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:12,840
It was a few days
before Hong Kong's handover.

71
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,480
POWER OUTAGE NOTICE

72
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,600
What's wrong, Uncle Wang?

73
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,520
Xu,

74
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,680
why is your place
making that banging noise?

75
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,840
My dad wants to sell the big wardrobe.

76
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:56,120
The doorway's too narrow.
Can't get it out.

77
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:59,200
So I thought I'd chisel
the doorframe a bit.

78
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,360
Why sell it?

79
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,280
There's a qigong master in Yuanlongli

80
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,880
who claims he can cure anything.

81
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,240
He's just expensive.

82
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:09,640
Oh…

83
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,040
Uncle Wang,

84
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,760
you…

85
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:16,120
I've got mung bean soup cooking at home.

86
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,320
It's going to burn.

87
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,520
It's going to burn.

88
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:20,600
It's burning…

89
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,800
30TH MONDAY

90
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:39,200
That wardrobe was still inside, not sold.

91
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:42,200
The scrap collector came the next day

92
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:44,680
and haggled with Xu for a long time.

93
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:47,480
In the end, they didn't
reach a deal on the wardrobe,

94
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:50,040
so he just took away
a bunch of jars and bottles.

95
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,160
How about this?

96
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,200
Call the person who hired you

97
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:02,920
and tell him the 500 is up.

98
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,320
Ask him to send you more.

99
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,760
Do you have the number?

100
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,200
Let me check.

101
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,280
Still here.

102
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,920
This one.

103
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,600
A Guangdong number?

104
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,400
I haven't called it in years.

105
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:30,360
<i>Hello. The number you have dialed</i>
<i>is no longer in service.</i>

106
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,640
<i>Please check and dial again.</i>

107
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,640
<i>Sorry, the subscriber you dialed…</i>

108
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:36,400
<i>Please check and dial again.</i>

109
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:40,440
<i>Hello. The number you have dialed</i>
<i>is no longer in service.</i>

110
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,200
<i>Please check and dial again.</i>

111
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:52,960
<i>Hello. The number you have dialed</i>
<i>is no longer in service.</i>

112
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,880
<i>Please check and dial again.</i>

113
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:59,040
How did it become a dead number?

114
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,600
Even this last bit of hope is gone.

115
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,240
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

116
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:10,920
<i>Freedom, freedom</i>

117
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:14,720
<i>Close your eyes</i>
<i>And get a good night's sleep</i>

118
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,760
<i>Run, run</i>
<i>Leave the past behind</i>

119
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:21,200
<i>No matter the outcome, it doesn't matter</i>

120
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Why did it stop?

121
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:47,120
Who let you sneak the instruments out?

122
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,160
Dad,

123
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,280
we just borrowed them for a bit.

124
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,000
We'll take good care of them.

125
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:54,760
SLOW

126
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:55,840
Nothing will get damaged.

127
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,520
What did I tell you?

128
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,480
If you want to start a band,

129
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,560
bring me a university
admission letter in exchange.

130
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,320
Did you take that as nothing?

131
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,320
Move everything back!

132
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,400
I'll deal with you when you get home.

133
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,560
Uncle.

134
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,400
We've written a new song.

135
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,160
Do you want to hear it?

136
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:24,480
Maybe after you listen,

137
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,720
you'll support our rock dream.

138
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,960
Rock dream?

139
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,440
Is that something
students should be doing?

140
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,080
Look at you all,

141
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,800
one worse than the next,
acting like hooligans.

142
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,480
Instead of studying properly at home,

143
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,680
you mess around all day.

144
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,920
What future will you have?

145
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,440
Are you moving it or not?

146
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,800
Not moving it, right?

147
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,240
Dad.

148
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,720
- Let go.
- Don't grab it.

149
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,560
- Let go.
- Don't grab it.

150
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,200
Keyboard!

151
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:14,080
PUBLIC SECURITY

152
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:16,520
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

153
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:20,320
Captain, before Han Zi'ang
injured someone,

154
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,320
he was very likely attacked.

155
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,880
Explain. How did you come
to that conclusion?

156
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,360
When I went to Yuanlongli to investigate,

157
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,400
I ran into my dad.

158
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:30,920
He and Ran

159
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:36,120
once carried out an immersive reenactment.

160
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:41,280
I know my dad wasn't in the clearest
state of mind back then,

161
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,960
but I believe Captain Ran's theory
is sound.

162
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,400
The Han Zi'ang case

163
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,560
is definitely more than just a prank.

164
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,240
MODERN LAW ENFORCEMENT
UNWAVERING POLICE EXCELLENCE

165
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:54,880
Yesterday, I also
made a pledge to the principal.

166
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,920
Within a week,

167
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,840
I'll prove that Han Zi'ang acted
in self defense.

168
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:01,480
Otherwise, he'll be expelled.

169
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,120
Captain, can you assign me more manpower?

170
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,880
Xiaohe,

171
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:15,000
I understand how you feel.

172
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,200
You want to find the truth

173
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,760
and help Han Zi'ang.

174
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,880
But the situation in the unit,
you should know it too.

175
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,000
Those four kids still haven't been found.

176
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:25,680
Everyone… Right now, everyone
is tied up with the task force.

177
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,560
You're relying on Mr. He and Ran…

178
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,160
Just on a few of Mr. He's deductions,

179
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,280
with no evidence, no leads.

180
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,760
Then tell me,

181
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,400
how am I supposed to ask
the task force for people?

182
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,840
FREE REFILLS, HELP YOURSELF

183
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:03,400
Why the long face?

184
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,960
Is the cafeteria food that bad?

185
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,520
It's not bad,

186
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,800
it just feels awful.

187
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:17,680
The Han Zi'ang case?

188
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,520
I don't have a single lead right now.

189
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,760
And my dad keeps making things worse.

190
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,840
This is my first case.

191
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,400
If only Uncle Ran were here,

192
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,120
he'd never let me turn in a blank.

193
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,160
In the whole Nanshan Branch,

194
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:37,040
people who say that
could line up to the gate.

195
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:41,040
When you handle cases,
if all you do is rely on Captain Ran,

196
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:42,960
then do you know,

197
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,880
back then, Captain Ran
also had someone he relied on?

198
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,000
Who?

199
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:48,080
Someone even more impressive
than Uncle Ran?

200
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,200
One time after working late,
I went for a late-night snack

201
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,360
and ran into your Uncle Ran
at the entrance.

202
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:55,360
He seemed troubled.

203
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:58,520
That was the first time I saw him drink.

204
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:01,440
He told me

205
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:04,240
the person he respected most
from the bottom of his heart

206
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,120
was your dad.

207
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,520
He also said, if not for your dad,

208
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,040
he wouldn't have made it
this far so smoothly.

209
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,160
He might not have even gotten through
his very first case.

210
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,600
When did that happen?

211
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,680
Around 2002, I think.

212
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,400
Time flies.

213
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,320
It's been 12 years
since Captain Ran passed.

214
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:39,640
If you want to look
into Han Zi'ang's case,

215
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:41,760
you'd better ask
the experts from Yuanlongli.

216
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:43,840
There are two experts in the unit.

217
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,960
One was Captain Ran back then,

218
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:48,200
and the other is your dad.

