00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,640
Did something happen?

267
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,000
It's not me. It's the keyboard player.

268
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,800
His dad came today,

269
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,920
took all the instruments, and beat him up.

270
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,440
Why are adults always like this?

271
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:17,120
Why can't they support our dreams?

272
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,880
Didn't they have dreams
when they were young?

273
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,760
Maybe when they chased their dreams,

274
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,400
they stumbled too many times,

275
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:32,800
so they don't want you
to go through the same thing.

276
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,520
Whether his dad has dreams, I don't know,

277
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,560
but my dad definitely doesn't have any.

278
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,840
Otherwise, my mom wouldn't
have gotten so mad, she left home.

279
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:58,160
BANK

280
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:34,040
CONTACT: YUN, MAKE A CALL?

281
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,320
CONTACT: YUN

282
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:41,240
CALLING YUN

283
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:42,160
END CALL

284
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:35,280
- What are you doing?
- Noise. Disturbing the peace.

285
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:37,760
Leave my room immediately.

286
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:38,880
He.

287
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:47,160
Look at her,
acting completely out of control.

288
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,720
Take it easy.

289
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,360
Leave it to me.

290
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:18,760
How did you do that?
What did you say to her?

291
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,120
Nothing much.
Just gave her a pair of headphones.

292
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:25,000
Eat first.

293
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:27,040
There's more in the pot
if it's not enough.

294
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,080
Let's talk business.
I'll brief you on the case.

295
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,440
The Forensic Department

296
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:40,400
found signs of arsenic poisoning
in Xu Zhihong's skull.

297
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:42,880
At the Xu residence,

298
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,480
I found some herbal residue.

299
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:46,440
I've already handed it over to Liang Juan.

300
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:49,440
The test report should be out tomorrow.

301
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,200
Zhang…

302
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,520
Zhang Ersong.

303
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:57,560
Who?

304
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:02,280
Master Zhang from 1713 Qihuang Clinic.

305
00:24:02,360 --> 00:24:04,760
This should be the prescription
he gave Xu Zhihong.

306
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:06,760
I found out Xu Zhihong
once had a huge argument

307
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:07,800
with Zhang Ersong.

308
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,080
He even threatened to expose him.

309
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:11,280
The two fell out badly.

310
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:12,800
Zhang Ersong

311
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,600
deliberately poisoned him?

312
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:24,560
<i>The skin of mung beans is green.</i>
<i>It belongs to wood.</i>

313
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:25,320
QIGONG MASTER, ZHANG ERSONG

314
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:28,960
<i>When boiled into soup, it turns yellow,</i>
<i>which belongs to earth.</i>

315
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,640
<i>This spirited,</i>

316
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:32,680
<i>energetic elderly gentleman</i>

317
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:34,600
<i>is the renowned healer of Beijing,</i>

318
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,120
<i>a third generation inheritor,</i>

319
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,080
<i>Master Zhang Ersong.</i>

320
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:40,040
<i>Mung beans and eggplant,</i>

321
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:42,400
<i>together complete the five elements.</i>

322
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:47,200
THE MEDICINAL DREGS DELIVERED YESTERDAY
CONTAINED TRACE ARSENIC.

323
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,800
<i>Songbentang Traditional Medicine Clinic</i>

324
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:54,440
<i>was founded by Master Zhang Ersong,</i>

325
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:56,720
<i>a third generation healer of Beijing.</i>

326
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:58,600
- <i>Master Zhang Ersong</i>
- Zhang Ersong.

327
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,600
<i>is like Hua Tuo reborn.</i>

328
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:01,640
What are you here for?

329
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,840
- Registration number?
- What number?

330
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:06,520
To see Master Zhang, you need to register.

331
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,240
This number should work, right?

332
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:09,240
I don't care who you are.

333
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:11,440
Even the mayor has to register.

334
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:13,400
And Master Zhang is off today,
no consultations.

335
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:17,960
Zhang Ersong,

336
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,880
a relative from your hometown
in Langzhong is here.

337
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,880
Your home is in Chentang County,

338
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,960
Maquan Township, Wumaganzhi Village.

339
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:26,400
At 25, you committed fraud
and served time.

340
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:28,120
- At 28…
- <i>Zhao,</i>

341
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,600
<i>let this patient in.</i>

342
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:33,320
<i>You can tell at a glance</i>
<i>he's seriously ill.</i>

343
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,240
Alright.

344
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,120
Go on in.

345
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,440
BENEVOLENT HEART, DIVINE HEALING

346
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:43,760
A MIRACLE HEALER, A BENEVOLENT MASTER

347
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,160
Please have a look, both of you.

348
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:54,440
WEIYANG PEOPLE'S HOSPITAL
MEDICAL DIAGNOSIS

349
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:55,440
Officers,

350
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,520
I've truly been wronged.

351
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,600
The prescription I gave Xu Zhihong

352
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:03,120
was something I developed
through years of research.

353
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:05,600
Even now that I'm ill,

354
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,600
I'm still using the same prescription.

355
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:13,320
What exactly is in
this prescription of yours?

356
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:16,440
That's a trade secret.

357
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,520
A proprietary formula.

358
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:22,400
You added a large amount
of realgar to this medicine, didn't you?

359
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:23,960
How do you know?

360
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,880
Realgar contains a high amount of arsenic.

361
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,440
Long term excessive use

362
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:31,800
can lead to arsenic poisoning.

363
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:33,320
You…

364
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:35,480
You're not trying to fool me, are you?

365
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,040
Hospital reports don't lie, do they?

366
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:43,680
Anyone with basic scientific knowledge
would understand that.

367
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,960
This is the first time I've seen

368
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:49,080
someone poison others
and not spare himself.

369
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:54,680
Tell me,

370
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:57,520
that Xu Zhihong,
why did he want to expose you?

371
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:01,240
That was due to his frostbite condition.

372
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,000
How would I know?

373
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,440
After Xu Zhihong got the medicine,

374
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:06,880
he started pestering me,

375
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:08,720
demanding a refund,

376
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,560
even threatening to go to the media.

377
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:12,520
You tell me,

378
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:14,760
how could I not get
into a conflict with him?

379
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,680
A conflict is one thing,

380
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:20,600
but it wouldn't escalate
to the level of murder.

381
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,000
The key is…

382
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,600
The key is, I already refunded his money.

383
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:36,040
REFUND RECEIPT

384
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:41,080
Before you moved out of Yuanlongli,

385
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:43,000
did you encounter anything unusual?

386
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:45,120
If you're asking about the case,

387
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,880
I really don't know.

388
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:49,160
But if you want gossip,

389
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:50,880
back in those days at Qihuang Clinic,

390
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,400
there was gossip every day.

391
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:54,440
The property manager, Qian Dajun,

392
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:56,440
used to moonlight at my place,
reselling appointment slots.

393
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:58,480
Cripple Du from the steel factory

394
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:00,360
and Song Qingsong from the cement plant

395
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:02,840
both came to me for kidney issues.

396
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:05,720
But Song Qingsong didn't come often.

397
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:07,920
The membership card he got
was used by his brother-in-law.

398
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:09,920
And Jin Manshan from Jinsha Market

399
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:12,480
also came to me for heart treatment.

400
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:17,760
Back then, someone
came to me to practice qigong,

401
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:20,920
saying he wanted to treat
his strange condition.

402
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:21,960
A strange condition?

403
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:24,520
He said he had a peculiar habit.

404
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:27,520
He couldn't be with women,

405
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:29,960
yet he liked collecting women's clothing

406
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:33,560
and watching women's bodies
from a distance.

407
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,320
Who was that person?

408
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,240
I remember now.

409
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:44,240
Xu Zhihong was introduced by him.

410
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:46,320
He even said Xu Meng was his god-sister.

411
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:49,920
You could tell right away
it wasn't a proper relationship.

412
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,360
Who exactly was it?

413
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:53,800
Didn't I just mention him?

414
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,800
Wu Shanlong.

415
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:08,960
Hello?

416
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:10,040
<i>Officer He,</i>

417
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:11,840
<i>the video rental shop owner</i>
<i>you asked me to find</i>

418
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:12,840
<i>has been arrested at the station.</i>

419
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:20,680
PUBLIC SECURITY

420
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,720
I'd like to ask,

421
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:31,000
for producing obscene discs,

422
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:32,520
how long would I be sentenced?

423
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:35,640
If I provide clues
about the severed head case,

424
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:38,120
would that count as meritorious service?

425
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,440
Wu Zhengxiong.

426
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:43,600
Whether it counts as meritorious service

427
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,120
depends on whether
the information you provide

428
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,160
is actually useful.

429
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:47,840
It'll definitely be useful.

430
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:49,640
Back in '97,

431
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:51,120
someone came to the video rental shop

432
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:52,920
to hire Wolfie to kill someone.

433
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,640
I took note of that person back then.

434
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:56,880
Why didn't you report it at the time?

435
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,000
Officer,

436
00:29:58,520 --> 00:30:00,000
I'm just an ordinary citizen.

437
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,880
How would I dare
offend people from that world?

438
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:05,600
Besides, I don't have nine lives.

439
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:07,280
Cut the nonsense.

440
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,640
Who was that person?

441
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:12,400
Song Qingsong's brother-in-law,
Wu Shanlong.

442
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:14,720
I saw him clearly back then.

443
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:15,960
He was even driving that Mercedes

444
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:18,040
with the license ending in 688.

445
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,840
- Are you sure?
- I'm sure.

446
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:23,200
Officer, I'm very good
at remembering faces.

447
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:26,080
Back then, Jin Manshan
and his subordinate, Hu Anping,

448
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,840
even took me to the entrance of Dahuihuang
to identify him in person.

449
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:33,200
Officer,

450
00:30:33,720 --> 00:30:35,400
I've told you almost everything.

451
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,000
About my case…

452
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:39,040
- In this case…
- Han.

453
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:42,000
- What is it, Officer He?
- Your turn.

454
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:43,040
Alright.

455
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:46,160
Officer, does this count
as meritorious service?

456
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,000
- Officer.
- Sit down.

457
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:53,040
He, let's go to Hongyun Huihuang Club.

458
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:54,000
Let's go.

459
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:55,480
Hold on.

460
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:00,760
- What were those words?
- What does that mean?

461
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:03,120
You take the lead, I'll back you up.

462
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:05,480
You go upfront, I stay behind.
You play it clean, I handle the rough.

463
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:09,000
What kind of coordination is that?

464
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,240
Catching him is what matters.

465
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:11,280
Let's go.

466
00:31:11,360 --> 00:31:13,320
I really can't believe this.

467
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,400
In broad daylight,

468
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:19,080
someone actually dares
to assault a law abiding citizen.

469
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,560
And you're still sitting there?

470
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,080
How are you enforcing the law?

471
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:23,200
Why are you just sitting there?

472
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,080
Go catch him.

473
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,560
Do you have no sense of compassion at all?

474
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:29,600
Look at this. You won't
even pour me a cup of tea.

475
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:31,800
Is this how you treat an injured person?

476
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:35,760
I came here to report a case,

477
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:40,000
so why does it feel like
I'm the one being interrogated?

478
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:44,840
You two officers,
aren't you criminal police?

479
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,720
Why are you working at the station?

480
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:47,640
Wu Shanlong,

481
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:49,480
you should know very well

482
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,000
why we're here.

483
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,200
I don't know. How would I know?

484
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,560
You don't know?

485
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:55,680
Fine.

486
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:57,440
Start by explaining
what happened to your head.

487
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:00,480
Someone tried to harm me.

488
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,560
In broad daylight,

489
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:03,880
he tried to smash my head open.

490
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:08,040
Who tried to harm you? Tell it in detail.

491
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:09,600
After we met yesterday,

492
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:11,280
I was about to drive home.

493
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:14,360
I don't know who put
a stone under my tire.

494
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:15,920
So I got out, and when
I was moving that stone,

495
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,160
suddenly, someone appeared behind me,

496
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,440
and then bang,

497
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:22,760
hit the back of my head.

498
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:24,440
Luckily, I've trained
in martial arts before.

499
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:25,360
My reflexes were fast.

500
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:28,640
Otherwise, my head
would've been split in two.

501
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:30,200
Was there anyone else at the scene?

502
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:33,120
I left through the back door.

503
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,120
No one saw anything.

504
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:40,040
This is the weapon
the attacker left behind.

505
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,360
Take it and run tests.

506
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:43,600
The attacker's fingerprints must be on it.

507
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:46,240
Right now, it's all
your fingerprints on it.

508
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:55,600
Who do you think attacked you?

509
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:57,360
I don't know who it was.

510
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,720
Maybe someone saw
I was driving a Mercedes,

511
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:01,440
thought I had money, and tried to rob me.

512
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:04,440
After knocking me out,
they realized I was broke.

513
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:09,040
Don't worry,

514
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:10,840
we'll take this seriously.

515
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:12,720
Do you have anything else to add?

516
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,200
No.

517
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,680
Then that's all.

518
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:27,000
I can leave now, right?

519
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:29,520
Who said you could leave?
We still have more questions.

520
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:32,520
Repeat what you said yesterday
at Hongyun Huihuang Club.

521
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:34,080
Didn't I already say it yesterday?

522
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:35,760
- It's only been a day…
- Cut the nonsense.

523
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:37,000
Say it.

524
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:42,840
A few years ago,
Song Qingsong gave me 40,000

525
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:44,640
to get rid of Xu Meng and her father.

526
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:47,080
He may not know the law, but I do.
I couldn't possibly do what he asked…

527
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,960
What you said doesn't match
your earlier statement.

528
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,160
It's the same.

529
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:55,560
There's no difference. It's the same.

530
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:58,240
Song Qingsong, 40,000,

531
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,960
Xu Meng and her father. I didn't do it.

532
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,160
Then…

533
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:03,240
Wu Shanlong,

534
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:07,320
someone reported that you hired Wolfie
to kill Xu Meng and her father.

535
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:09,440
Who said that? Who said it?

536
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:10,560
That's slander.

537
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,400
A false accusation.
This is clearly a frame up…

538
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,800
Wu Shanlong.

539
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:15,840
According to the Criminal Law
of the People's Republic of China,

540
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:17,520
Articles 25 and 29,

541
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,600
hiring someone to kill is punished

542
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:21,400
as joint intentional homicide.

543
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:23,679
The person who hires
is considered an instigator

544
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:25,440
and bears primary criminal responsibility.

545
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:27,719
That's impossible.
Someone must be framing me.

546
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,280
- Impossible.
- Think carefully.

547
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:32,400
Will you confess for leniency
or resist and face harsher punishment?

548
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,159
Confess.

549
00:34:42,159 --> 00:34:43,320
I'll confess.

550
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:46,080
I did hire Wolfie.

551
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,880
Song Qingsong instructed

552
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:50,280
that Xu Meng and her father
be driven out of Weiyang.

553
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,199
I only meant to scare them away.

554
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,960
I never intended to kill anyone.

555
00:34:54,040 --> 00:34:56,280
Besides, Wolfie never acted.

556
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:57,880
- So…
- If Wolfie didn't act,

557
00:34:57,960 --> 00:34:59,520
then how did Xu Meng and her father die?

558
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:01,600
- Did you hire someone else?
- No.

559
00:35:01,680 --> 00:35:03,640
- Or did you do it yourself?
- How could that be?

560
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,600
It has nothing to do with me.
I didn't do anything.

561
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:08,080
Stop playing tricks.

562
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,640
I don't know anything anymore.

563
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:13,800
I don't know anything now.
Go ask Song Qingsong.

564
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:14,920
I don't know anything. Ask Song Qingsong.

565
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,240
I want to go home now.

566
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:20,920
Playing dumb,

567
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:22,440
digging in his heels.

568
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:25,600
He's definitely still hiding something.

569
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:27,720
Since Wu Zhengxiong has pointed to him,

570
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:30,360
then let's just detain him for 48 hours,

571
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,400
wear him down, then press him again.

572
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:33,760
He,

573
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:36,400
Wu Shanlong came in as a reporting victim.

574
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:38,240
We have no direct evidence

575
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:39,480
and no detention warrant.

576
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:41,720
If he keeps making a scene,

577
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:43,200
we'll only end up more passive.

578
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:45,160
Wait here. I'll go back
to the bureau and get one issued.

579
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:46,400
Hold on.

580
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:48,280
Let him go first.

581
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,800
See what he does.

582
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:52,360
If there really are accomplices
or anything hidden,

583
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,480
once he's out, he'll make a move.

584
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:58,920
I'm just angry.

585
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:01,360
This guy has played us so many times,

586
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:04,680
and now he's still out there living it up,

587
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:06,480
free for five whole years.

588
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,760
That's exactly why those
five years have cost us so much.

589
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:11,320
Many clues and evidence

590
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:12,840
are now hard to track down.

591
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,200
We might as well let him show his hand,

592
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:16,760
then use that chance to break through.

593
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:19,400
Don't worry. I'll keep an eye on him.

594
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,640
Then we cover both ends.

595
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:23,080
I'll go find Jin Manshan

596
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:25,040
and see if I can get anything out of him.

597
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:28,720
Jin Manshan got involved
in organized crime three years ago

598
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:29,840
and fled.

599
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:33,080
The big one may run,

600
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:34,120
but the small one won't.

601
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:42,600
PUBLIC SECURITY

602
00:37:03,040 --> 00:37:04,280
Let's go to Yuanlongli.

603
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:30,400
SWISH!

604
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:33,040
BANG!

605
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:39,640
Take a break.

606
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:41,680
Eat while it's hot.

607
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:44,600
I'll eat later.

608
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:46,200
What do you mean later?

609
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:48,680
By the time you remember,
I'll have cooked the next meal.

610
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:49,760
I'm watching you.

611
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:51,160
Eat it now.

612
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:02,080
By the way,

613
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:04,320
did that kid say anything today?

614
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:08,760
He's developed acute stress.

615
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:10,320
He hasn't said a word,

616
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:11,720
completely shut himself off.

617
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:14,800
Right now,

618
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:17,360
I'm reading the comics he used to read,
trying to find a breakthrough.

619
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:20,800
His mother said he usually just reads,

620
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:22,080
doesn't play games or hang out online.

621
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:23,920
I just can't figure out

622
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:26,520
why he skipped school
and went to Yuanlongli.

623
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:28,400
Times change.

624
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:29,840
Energy is limited.

625
00:38:30,360 --> 00:38:32,040
Focus on the important.
Let go of the trivial.

626
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,880
Food and clothing come first.

627
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:35,920
What does that mean?

628
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,680
It means when you investigate,

629
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:40,400
you have to rely on common sense.

630
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:42,640
What Han Zi'ang's mother said

631
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,680
can't be taken at face value.

632
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:47,000
That doesn't mean
she's lying to the police,

633
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:50,160
but how many parents nowadays

634
00:38:50,240 --> 00:38:52,640
truly understand their children?

635
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:55,640
Especially teenagers.

636
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,840
Just like back then,

637
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:59,040
you didn't understand me either.

638
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:01,600
So,

639
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:05,880
what Han Zi'ang's mother sees
may just be the side

640
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:08,680
he wants her to see.

641
00:39:08,760 --> 00:39:10,880
Maybe Han Zi'ang

642
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:13,280
does like gaming and hanging out online.

643
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,400
That makes sense.

644
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:18,520
At his age,

645
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:20,160
legal internet cafes won't admit him.

646
00:39:20,240 --> 00:39:21,440
He can only go to unlicensed ones.

647
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:25,240
But there aren't any in Yuanlongli.

648
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:27,280
If you can find them,

649
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:30,120
they wouldn't be unlicensed, would they?

650
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:36,640
LASER ENGRAVING. CUSTOM GIFTS

651
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:50,360
JUAN JUAN SHOE SHOP

652
00:39:50,440 --> 00:39:52,120
LIANG'S COMPUTER SUPPLIES

653
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:53,040
Miss.

654
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,720
Where's your boss?

655
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:57,520
He stepped out.

656
00:39:57,600 --> 00:40:00,080
I've already asked this shop before.
No useful leads.

657
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:01,240
Let's hurry and check the internet cafes.

658
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:08,760
- Dad.
- Sir.

659
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:25,640
Heal him.

660
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,400
Druid, you can't heal?

661
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:33,680
Uncle He, you scared me.

662
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,640
At least say something first.

663
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:36,800
You're the owner here, right?

664
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:40,120
Why are you running
an illegal internet cafe

665
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:41,600
and letting minors play games?

666
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:43,520
Officer?

667
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:44,640
Officer, you've misunderstood.

668
00:40:44,720 --> 00:40:45,840
I'm not running an illegal place.

669
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:47,160
I have a license. A license?

670
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:50,280
I just can't stand seeing kids
having nowhere to play.

671
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:51,400
That's why I let them in.

672
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:53,200
What I'm doing
is basically a public service.

673
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:54,240
I don't charge anything.

674
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:56,840
Really. I can swear on my game logs.

675
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:02,440
Alright, don't make things hard for Du.

676
00:41:02,520 --> 00:41:05,600
He's an old acquaintance
of both me and your Uncle Ran.

677
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:06,560
Really.

678
00:41:10,600 --> 00:41:11,520
Let me ask you again.

679
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:13,000
Have you seen this kid?

680
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,320
I already told you earlier,

681
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:18,600
I haven't seen him.

682
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:21,880
You can go ask outside.

683
00:41:26,640 --> 00:41:28,520
- Uncle He, your daughter
- Hey, boy.

684
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:29,840
- is fierce.
- Excuse me.

685
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,000
Have you seen this kid before?

686
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:32,680
Takes after her dad.

687
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,640
Born to be a criminal investigator.

688
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:36,360
That's right.

689
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:38,600
Hey, excuse me.

690
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:39,800
Have you seen this kid?

691
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:41,080
No.

692
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:44,320
Hi. Have you seen this kid?

693
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:45,960
No.

694
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:49,000
Wait.

695
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:52,680
I've seen him.

696
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:55,960
Last week, he was at that computer
watching role playing stuff,

697
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:57,160
laughing while watching,

698
00:41:57,240 --> 00:41:59,040
even speaking some Japanese.

699
00:41:59,120 --> 00:42:01,200
Definitely a hardcore anime fan.

700
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,440
Pull up photos of those four kids.

701
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,920
Excuse me. Can I use your computer?

702
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:15,520
These four, have you seen them?

703
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:17,640
Haven't seen them.

704
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,080
What about you? Have you seen them?

705
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:24,320
This one, I've seen.

706
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:25,560
SPREAD THE NEWS: THESE KIDS ARE MISSING

707
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:27,120
This one, I've seen too.
